  "body": "Today I wrote a message in our `#travel-requests` channel. The message was formatted like a description list a la\r\n\r\n```\r\n**Item**: Description\r\n**Item2**: Description2\r\n**Item3**: Description3 \r\n```\r\netc. Unfortunately I don't have a screenshot of the original message anymore, but after noticing that there was a typo, I've edited the message, fixed the typo, and after saving the message looked like this:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-05-15 10-46-43](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/445106/eddc429c-1662-4254-827d-9d931ad08848)\r\n\r\nSome things broke here:\r\n\r\n- All description items lost their formatting (eg `Event`, `Date`, `Goal` etc should be bold)\r\n- The mention of  @jrainville just... got neutralized or something?\r\n\r\nI know we have a bunch of problems with message formatting, but I wasn't expecting it to be gone entirely + mentions breaking after editing a message.",
